Sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: OVCA429 cells were treated with PBS or IFNg for 3 hours.
Sample_growth_protocol_ch1: OVCA429 cells was cultured  as previously reported.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Cell nuclei were isolated and subjected to transposase for 30 minutes under active shaking (Buenrostro et al., 2013; Corces et al., 2017). Then, the purified tagged genomic DNA was amplified to generate illumine NGS library with Nextera DNA Sample Preparation Kit (Illumina, #FC-121-1030). The DNA size selection was done with Ampure beads (Beckman Coulter). The library was measured by bioanalyzer. Sequencing was performed by paired-end 50-mer sequencing in replicates at University of Michigan with HiSeq 2500 (Illumina)., Then, the purified tagged genomic DNA was amplified to generate illumine NGS library with Nextera DNA Sample Preparation Kit.
Sample_data_processing: The sequenced raw reads of each sample were aligned to the human reference genome GRCh38 using Novoalign., BAM files were created using SAMtools, and removed for duplicated reads or mitochondria reads., Reads were further filtered to identify nucleosome-free, open chromosomal regions., MACS2 was used to call ATAC-seq peaks, from which differentially accessible regions were determined by limma and EdgeR., The coverage tracks were generated using the program bam2wig.
Supplementary_files_format_and_content: bigWig file indicating peak intensity at open chromosomal regions
